    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-03T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-03T23:00:00-05:00" n="221"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3928: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to"
                            >Cunningham</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-03T23:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 3, 1932—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 3, 9 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Department approves your joining your colleagues in making representations
                        in the sense indicated.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Department has already on basis of your February 3, 2 a.m. and other data
                        instructed Ambassador Tokyo to make a fourth set of representations on this
                            subject.<note n="47" xml:id="d221fn47">See telegram No. 37, February 3,
                            5 p.m., to the Ambassador in Japan, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_179">
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                    rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 179</ref>.</note> British Government
                        had instructed British Ambassador Tokyo to make such representations and had
                        suggested to French and Italian Governments they take similar action.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Inform Nanking and Legation.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
